description.narrative: The development objective (PDO) is to enable consumers in selected areas to access heating appliances and services producing less particulate matter emissions and to further develop selected medium-term particulate matter abatement measures in Ulaanbaatar in coordination with development partners.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :FA Sch. 2, Sec. I. A. Provision of Financing to the Project Implementing Entity | Description :The obligation ofthe Recipient to make the entire proceeds of the IDA credit available to the UB municipality (Project Implementing Entity) underterms and conditions approved by the Association | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Sch. 2, Sec. II. A Quarterly report | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall prepare and furnishquarterly project reports not later than 30 days after the end of the period of the report. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :FA Sch. 2, Sec. II. B. Audited Financial Statements | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall furnishaudits and audited financial statements for a period of one fiscal year not later than s6 months after the end of the period. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Sch. 2, Sec. II. B. Quarterly interim unaudited financial reports | Description :The Project ImplementingEntity shall have prepare and furnish interim unaudited financial statements 45 days after the end of eachcalendar quarter. |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :PA, Sch., Sec. I. A. Institutional Arrangements, Para. 1 & 2 | Description :The Project Implementing Entityshall maintain a Steering Committee and a Project Management Unit with responsibilities for ProjectImplementation. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA. Sch., Sec. I. E. Operations Manual and Institutional Manual | Description :The Project Implementing Entityshall carry out the Project in accordance with the Operations Manual and the Institutional Manual. | Frequency :Yearly
